\par \plain\f8\fs20 We describe here, how a phase phile is structured and what the released file phrase.a99 contains.
\par There are two kinds of phrases: the \plain\f8\fs20\b Strg phrases \plain\f8\fs20 and the \plain\f8\fs20\b Esc Phrases\plain\f8\fs20 . They differ by the way they are activated: by the Strg key and by an Esc character, resp. (see below).
\par There can be only one  \plain\f8\fs20\i Strg\plain\f8\fs20  phrase per \plain\f8\fs20\i letter\plain\f8\fs20 , and one additional \plain\f8\fs20\i Esc\plain\f8\fs20   phrase for every \plain\f8\fs20\i alphanumeric character\plain\f8\fs20  .
\par Every Phrase may contain text (at least 1 character) or a FLEX  (beginning with  "x " or "X  " ).
